The paper discusses security vulnerabilities in processor hardware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of automated methods for detecting these vulnerabilities, which could fall under the categories of computer architecture (cs.AR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of these processors in applications such as Internet-of-Things and Autonomous Systems, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
